content:
To include the location ID for point of sale (POS) orders, you can add a new column for the location ID and pass in the `location_id` property of the order if the `source_name` property is equal to `pos`.

Here's an example of how you can modify the script to include the location ID for POS orders:
```java
function getShopifyOrders() {
  var shop_url = 'YOUR_SHOP_URL';
  var access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN';

  var start_date = new Date();
  start_date.setMonth(start_date.getMonth() - 1);
  var end_date = new Date();

  var url = 'https://' + shop_url + '/admin/api/2023-03/orders.json?created_at_min=' + start_date.toISOString() + '&created_at_max=' + end_date.toISOString() + '&status=any';

  var headers = {
    'X-Shopify-Access-Token': access_token
  };

  var options = {
    'method': 'get',
    'headers': headers
  };

  var response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(url, options);

  var orders = JSON.parse(response.getContentText()).orders;

  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSheet();
  sheet.clearContents();
  sheet.appendRow(['Order ID', 'Customer Name', 'Total', 'Created At', 'Shipping Address Province', 'Shipping Line Title', 'Shipping Cost', 'Source', 'Location ID']);

  for (var i = 0; i < orders.length; i++) {
    var order = orders[i];
    var shipping_address_province = order.shipping_address ? order.shipping_address.province_code : '';
    var shipping_line_title = order.shipping_lines.length > 0 ? order.shipping_lines[0].title : '';
    var shipping_cost = order.shipping_lines.length > 0 ? order.shipping_lines[0].price : '';
    var order_source = order.source_name ? order.source_name : '';
    var location_id = order.source_name === 'pos' ? order.location_id : '';
    sheet.appendRow([order.id, order.customer.first_name + ' ' + order.customer.last_name, order.total_price, order.created_at, shipping_address_province, shipping_line_title, shipping_cost, order_source, location_id]);
  }
}
```
In this modified script, we add a new column for the location ID and pass in the `location_id` property of the order if the `source_name` property is equal to `pos`. Note that we use a ternary operator to handle cases where the `location_id` property is empty or null.

You can add additional columns for other order properties in a similar way by modifying the `sheet.appendRow()` method and passing in the corresponding order data for each column.
